<br>
So, disarm him, but why the mad push to invade, the utter crass diplomacy that has angered, outraged or estranged many who would have helped?<br>
The international community *is* for disarming him, it's just not wanting another great stupid FUBAR in a very sensitive area of the world. <br>
  Actually I woudl say that Collin Powell maybe about the only guy in that entire administration with any sense, brains or understanding of foreign policy and it's implementations. Be nice to hear what he thinks *privately* about his Leader and other stuff.<br>
<br>
If you don't realize that conspiracies and outrages perpetrated by *insert name of your own government here* don't happen, then frankly you ain't been checking up on current events and history for the past 50 years. Think the *back* of JFKs head was due to some bizarre backwards flying bullet? That the CIA and Mafia weren't in bed since the OSS and Luciano got involved in Sicily? (go check the CIA vs Castro, if you think I'm talking crap) <br>
  Wanna go back further in time? USA and Britian and the Chinese Opium Wars, those directly lead to the Chinese Revolution and the heroin addicts on our streets.<br>
  The Gestapo put rumours around that Stalin's army was disloyal, so Stalin killed nearly a MILLION of his own troops and  so decimated his officer corps that the highest ranking person left was a Colonel , *one* colonel. That's how the Germans went through Russia's army like corn.<br>
  The Dreyfuss Scandal in France, he was a Jewish officer, there was treason in the army, he got hit with trumped up evidence to bury it and he was Jewish so easy scapegoat in an anti-semitic climate.<br>
  Concealing the KNOWN fact of the Nazi death camps during World War2 and hushing up the concentration camps horror before hostilities in the Western press and military.<br>
  USA military's involvment in making sure that black men infected with syphilis were not treated so they could be studied.<br>
<br>
That's the tip of the iceberg, there must be a ton of crap we also do not know because it was silenced or the folk buried. North Korean submarines landing commandoes in South Korea, USA intelligence officer spying for Saddam, Iran-Contra, those are some of the more recent conspiracies and bizarre crap.<br>
<br>
If you *DO* trust your political leaders and security forces you are *NAIVE*. And since we know conspiracies *do* happen, why would you think Bush Jr is incapable of perpetrating one? Some other USA presidents have been caught out (or almost caught out) commiting them.<br>
<br>
As for The Boogie Man, until someone comes up with 100% incontroverrtable evidence he does not exist, I maintain the right to believe he *may exist* even if the odds are extremely slim :&gt;<br>
That's a humorous reply, but, while some folk may not like this,<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> it's the proper scientific way of looking at it</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
Hm, that's another good rant, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;the quasi-religion of Science and its <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>belief</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in its Laws and Dogma&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. No, I'm not anti-Science, quite the reverse in fact.<br>
<br>
&quot;Succesffuly debunked&quot;, like, em how?  This is a *debate*, I may be wrong in some *facts* (Without going over this entire debate, have I?), but a lot of this has been about personal beliefs and values--from all sides. You don 't *debunk* that, you can argue against it however. Oh and facts are incontrovertable things like dates of events, the Who Why and What when it comes to Human Events/Politics/Beliefs is largely guesstimates, agreed upon testimony that is recorded and so forth, that's why you talk--debate such things.<br>
<br>
Oh and I *like* to ramble, a debate is  a talk with another person or persons, it often involves many subjects, wanders around, and encroaches on many different topics. That's largely what makes it fun and lets you learn things. You start arguing over football and end up several hours later wondering what would have happend if the Roman Empire hadn't fallen <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Paraphrasing you: Saddam is holding down the extremists because he's a socialist...er..? <br>
 Folk *KNOW* he's a bastrd, you think everyone outside the USA is uninformed? (*wry grin...sort of riposte dig there*). Folk are concerned with any action taken agaisnt him may result in an even WORSE mess, and despite what some have said  the MAJORITY of folk know that is a very real possibility. Going in like a bull in a china shop = bad. This isn't Haiti you know. About the best hope is that the build up of military forces allows the USA/UK to say secretly to Sadam's generals <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;either he goes or YOU go, and we chose who's in power and destroy the NBC weapons, you can hang on and draw your pay as usual&quot;,</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and so resolve the problem. A war wthout *willing* UN backing would be very very bad, in a lot more ways than you seem to realize :/<br>
